Help Menu for MVP Profile Viewer Tool
Introduction Welcome to the MVP Profile Viewer Tool! This tool is designed to help you easily view and analyze the Microsoft MVP Activity list that you can export from the Microsoft MVP portal. It allows you to load a JSON file containing your MVP profile data and presents the information in a user-friendly interface.
Getting Started 1. Export Your Data: - Visit the https://mvp.microsoft.com/en-US/account/ - Navigate to the 'Privacy' section. - Select 'Download your data' to export your profile data in JSON format.
2. Load the JSON File: - In the tool, click on 'Select JSON File' to open the file dialog. - Browse and select the downloaded JSON file from your computer. - The tool will parse the file and display your profile information and activities.
Features - Load JSON Data: - File Selection: Use the file dialog to locate and load your MVP profile JSON file. - Data Parsing: The tool extracts your profile details and activity records from the selected JSON file. - Error Handling: If there’s an issue loading the file (e.g., incorrect format or missing file), an error message will alert you.
- Display Profile Information: - Profile Details: Your name, email, date of birth, headline, and biography will be displayed in the designated text boxes.
- Display Activities: - DataGridView: View your activities in a table format with columns for Date Created, Activity Type, Role, Technology Focus Area, Target Audience, Title, Description, URL, and High Impact. - Activity Count: See the total number of activities at the bottom of the interface. - Activity Type Counts: View the breakdown of activities by type in a pop-up message box. - Technology Focus Area Counts: View the breakdown of activities by technology focus area in a pop-up message box.
Menu Options - Select JSON File: Opens a dialog to select and load a new JSON file. - About: Displays information about the tool, including its version and developer credits. - Help: Opens this Help dialog with instructions on how to use the tool.
Tips for Best Use - Make sure your exported JSON file is complete and has not been modified manually. - If you encounter any issues, refer to the error messages provided for guidance. - Regularly update your profile data from the MVP portal to keep your records accurate.
For further assistance or feedback, please contact the tool’s support team.
This Help menu provides step-by-step instructions and details about the features, ensuring users can effectively utilize the tool to manage and view their Microsoft MVP profile data.
